VALUES ('e991245f-2dfd-4476-8118-c7aa90aeb1b3', 'Which choice completes the text with the most logical transition?', 'Honeybees communicate the location of food through a precise ''waggle dance'' that encodes direction and distance. Researchers studying a related stingless bee species expected to find the same dance. They discovered instead that these bees mark trails with scent. ______ the two species solve the same problem in entirely different ways.', NULL, '[{"id":"A","text":"In short,","is_correct":true,"explanation":"Correct: it summarizes the contrast just described into a single concluding generalization."},{"id":"B","text":"By contrast,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Incorrect: the final sentence sums up the difference already shown rather than introducing a new contrasting item."},{"id":"C","text":"Because of this,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Incorrect: the difference in methods is not caused by the scent discovery; the sentence restates the finding."},{"id":"D","text":"Granted,","is_correct":false,"explanation":"Incorrect: ''Granted'' concedes a counterpoint, but the sentence affirms the main observation."}]'::jsonb, 'A', 'Step 1 — Track the discovery
Instead of a dance, the stingless bees {{yellow:mark trails with scent}}, revealing two different methods.
Step 2 — Pick the summary
The final sentence restates the whole point compactly, so a summarizing ''In short'' fits.
Distractor analysis:
- B: ''By contrast'' would set up one item against another, but the contrast is already stated and now summarized.
- C: ''Because of this'' implies causation, but the sentence is a recap, not an effect.
- D: ''Granted'' concedes a counterpoint that the text does not raise.', 'Is the last sentence summing up the whole comparison or adding a brand-new contrast?', 'Expression of Ideas', 'Transitions', 'reading_writing', 'expression', 'TRA', NULL, 'medium', false, 'SAT', 'multiple_choice', true, true, 'scholaris_ai', '{"generator":"scholaris_ai_v1","model":"gemma-4-26b-a4b-it","original":true,"explanation_v2":true}'::jsonb, now(), now())
